				<h5 class="et_pb_toggle_title">What Are California Shutters?</h5>
				<div class="et_pb_toggle_content clearfix"><p><span>California or Plantation Shutters as they are sometimes called are upscale wooden or vinyl-based window coverings that can block out light by the movement of slats which line the interior of the product in a horizontal fashion.</span></p></div> <!-- .et_pb_toggle_content -->
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_toggle --><div class="et_pb_toggle et_pb_module et_pb_accordion_item et_pb_accordion_item_1  et_pb_toggle_close">
				
				
				<h5 class="et_pb_toggle_title">What is the difference between Roller blinds &amp; Solar Shades?</h5>
				<div class="et_pb_toggle_content clearfix"><p><strong>The main difference between roller blinds and solar shades is the openness and light filtering ability of the fabric which you are choosing.</strong><span> The fabrics in our famous roller blinds collection fashion 1% to 10% light filtering fabrics. Blackout fabric options are also available. Solar shades on the other hand are better for uses in commercial applications. For example, in large in industrial complex this with the large windows, a motorized solar shade made with a vinyl composite mesh is better than a softer polyester material. Another difference between Roller Blinds and Solar Shades is the light filtering methods of the fabrics in question. All our solar shades are defined by an openness percentage (of the composite-vinyl/polyester weave) rather than measuring the amount of light filtering directly. In other words, the more open a fabric is. The more-light it will let through. Finally, there are little price differences between these two collections, however prices can vary depending on chosen fabrics and upgrades.</span></p></div> <!-- .et_pb_toggle_content -->
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_toggle --><div class="et_pb_toggle et_pb_module et_pb_accordion_item et_pb_accordion_item_2  et_pb_toggle_close">
				
				
				<h5 class="et_pb_toggle_title">What motors do you use when automating roller blinds or shades?</h5>
				<div class="et_pb_toggle_content clearfix"><p><strong>We used France manufactured, Somfy motors</strong><span>, which are the best because of their durability, affordability and unique design. There are two main ways we can add motorization to your window coverings. The blind can be powered by your home or each unit can operate separately via battery power. With either option, we provide you with custom remotes and the universal hub that allows you to automate your blinds on your cellular device. You can also connect your blinds to smart hubs and apps like google home and Amazons echo systems.</span></p></div> <!-- .et_pb_toggle_content -->
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_toggle --><div class="et_pb_toggle et_pb_module et_pb_accordion_item et_pb_accordion_item_3  et_pb_toggle_close">
				
				
				<h5 class="et_pb_toggle_title">Why should I get California or Plantation Shutters?</h5>
				<div class="et_pb_toggle_content clearfix"><p><span>Plantation Shutters are simply beautiful. They are the only window fashion that you can put into any room of your house. Let’s face it California shutters, especially our hand-crafted shutter collections, look good in bathrooms, kitchen, on patio doors, in bay windows, mounted on skylights. In other words, shutters can change the ambiance of any window in any room.</span></p></div> <!-- .et_pb_toggle_content -->
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_toggle --><div class="et_pb_toggle et_pb_module et_pb_accordion_item et_pb_accordion_item_4  et_pb_toggle_close">
				
				
				<h5 class="et_pb_toggle_title">What are the most affordable window coverings in Toronto?</h5>
